This paper deals with online linear optimization, which is a topic in machine learning and optimization. The use of regularization functions and the analysis of performance bounds are common techniques in the field of machine learning, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also deals with matrices and their properties, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The use of sparse matrices and the application to online collaborative filtering suggest that the paper could also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Finally, the use of optimization techniques and the analysis of performance bounds suggest that the paper could belong to the cs.SI (Systems and Control) sub-category.
